  "prompt": "What is a good book to learn Excel?",
  "response": "There are several excellent books for learning Excel, catering to various skill levels. Here are a few highly recommended ones:\n\n1. **\"Excel 2021 for Dummies\" by Greg Harvey** - This is a user-friendly guide that covers the basics as well as some advanced features of Excel. It\u2019s perfect for beginners.\n\n2. **\"Excel 2019 Power Programming with VBA\" by Michael Alexander and Dick Kusleika** - If you're interested in mastering macros and VBA programming in Excel, this book provides comprehensive coverage.\n\n3. **\"Excel 2021 Power User\" by Michael Alexander and John Walkenbach** - This book is great for users who want to enhance their skills beyond the basics, focusing on advanced techniques and functions.\n\n4. **\"Excel Formulas and Functions For Dummies\" by Ken Bluttman** - This book is particularly useful if you're looking to deepen your understanding of Excel's powerful formulas and functions.\n\n5. **\"Data Analysis with Microsoft Excel\" by Kenneth N. Berk and Patrick M. Carey** - This book focuses on using Excel for data analysis, making it a great choice for those interested in applying Excel in data-driven fields.\n\nEach of these books offers valuable insights and techniques for improving your Excel skills. Choose one that aligns with your current level and learning objectives!",
